Kim Jong Il receives letter from NDFSK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a letter from the central committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea on July 8 on the occasion of the 6th anniversary of the passing away of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The last six years from the day of bitter grief when the nation suffered the greatest loss in its history to this day have been days during which all the people have more keenly realized the President was a peerlessly great man and a glorious history which unfolded the great reality that he is immortal with the era as the sun of Juche, the letter said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It said 80 odd year-long history of the President was the noblest and brilliant life of a gifted thinker and theoretician, an outstanding statesman, an invincible and iron-willed commander and a great man whom the nation and humankind acclaimed for the first time and held in high esteem. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It recalled that he, considering the reunification of the country as the supreme task of the nation, unrolled a great program for national reunification, consistently adhered to the line of national independence, and wisely led the work for the great national unity and the cause of national reunification until the last moments of his life, opening a new phase of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il, steering the cause of Juche together with the President for scores of years, has brilliantly adorned a glorious revolutionary history as the most outstanding man in the contemporary political history over the last six years, adding shine to the President's idea and cause single-handedly, the letter noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The revolutionary history of the President continues as Kim Jong Il's history of building a powerful nation and the President is immortal thanks to Kim Jong Il who performed immortal exploits, defending and exalting the idea and cause of the President with his noble sense of obligation and outstanding political ability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The letter expressed the determination to lift higher the banner of national independence and bring the popular masses' elated enthusiasm reunification into full display like an active volcano and thus carry out the President's last instructions for reunification without fail.

Kim Il Sung lauded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Thongsing Thammavong who visited the DPRK at the head of the delegation of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party said that the respected leader Kim Il Sung was a great revolutionary and a great man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His whole life is shining as the life of a great man who founded an idea for the popular masses and enforced politics for them, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The human history does not know such a popular leader as Kim Il Sung who performed great and immortal exploits, putting people above all and making endless trips for people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Il Sung, the greatest man and the publicly recognized leader of the world revolution, is always highly praised by all the people for the great exploits he performed for the development of both the Korean revolution and the world revolution.

Cambodian crew remember Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Wonsan, July 8 (KCNA) -- A meeting of the crew of the Cambodian ship "Sunrise-1" to remember the President Kim Il Sung was held in Wonsan port on the occasion of his 6th death anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Expressing deep reverence for President Kim Il Sung, a veteran statesman in the world and a great man, speakers said that he founded the Juche idea in his early years, shedding its bright rays all over the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The President always lives in the hearts of humankind as he performed great exploits for the Korean revolution and the realization of the human cause of independence, they stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A letter to General Secretary Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

Three-point charter of Korea's reunification supported 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- The international signature campaign supporting the three-point charter of Korea's reunification, which began in March in response to an appeal of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, is going on all over the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The signature paper was signed by over 330 political parties, social organizations and associations for friendship and solidarity in over 80 countries and regions and figures of all circles including leading personages of regional and international organizations on behalf of at least 98.9 million persons over the last more than 4 months since the campaign began. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The campaign was participated in by people of various circles including political, social, economic, military ones and media.

Colorful functions held in various countries 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Meetings to remember the President Kim Il Sung were held by the Group for the Study of Kimilsungism of Peru, the Group for the Study of Kimjongilism of Guinea, the Guinean Society for the Study of the Juche Literary Idea, the Misr al-Patat Party of Egypt and Cratori Cafete House of Culture of Portugal from June 28 to July 2 on the occasion of his 6th death anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Indian Society for the Study of Works of Kim Jong Il held a joint seminar on July 3 on the subject "President Kim Il Sung always lives in the hearts of progressive humankind." Seminars on the exploits of the President were held by the Indian Youth Group for the Study of Works of Comrade Kim Il Sung on June 30 and in the Czech Republic on July 3.

Japan's move for payment of "comfort money" condemned 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Measure Committee for Demanding Compensation to "Comfort Women for the Army" and the Victims of the Pacific War issued a statement yesterday condemning the recent Japanese diet passage of the bills on paying a petty amount of "comfort money" to Koreans in Japan who are former soldiers and employees of the Japanese imperial army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   According to the bills, the Japanese government is going to pay "comfort money" to a few bereaved families of the war dead and wounded veterans permanently resident in Japan out of those who were taken as soldiers and employees of the Japanese imperial army from Korea during World War II, even that much less than the money paid to former Japanese soldiers and employees, the statement said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This is another despicable charade betraying the crafty and shameless nature peculiar to Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The statement bitterly denounced this as an unbearable insult to the victims and the Korean nation and a challenge to justice and human conscience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Through this the Japanese government seeks to create impression that it is interested in the settlement of its past and calm down the growing public criticism, it said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Dismissing the Japanese government's payment of "comfort money" as hypocritical, the committee demands as follows: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Firstly, the Japanese government should fully own its legal responsibility as an assailant for the issue of the Korean soldiers and employees of the Japanese imperial army and make a state apology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Secondly, the compensation to the Korean soldiers and employees of the Japanese imperial army should involve all the Korean victims and bereaved families including the Koreans in Japan and compensation enough to convince them should be made for their mental and physical damage, distress caused by this and sufferings of their families. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   And it strongly urges the Japanese government to honestly apologize and compensate for all the criminal acts committed against the Korean people such as forcible walking away of Korean women as "comfort women for the army" and other crimes.

Chongryon holds lecture meeting 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, July 7 (KNS-KCNA) -- A lecture meeting of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) took place at the Korean Hall on July 7 on the occasion of the 6th anniversary of the passing away of the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the meeting were first vice-chairman So Man Sul, chief vice-chairman Ho Jong Man and other officials of the central standing committee of Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants listened to the recorded lecture "the fatherly leader is a great man with rare charisma".
